         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21.11.83. ¶  ¶ Herewith, dear Mr. Jackson, I beg to send you a copy of part of a letter from Dr. Fournier, just received, ¶  concerning the priority of  ¶ Vahea ¶  over  ¶ Landolphia ¶ , as this quest...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">83.11.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To B. Daydon Jackson</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from Gleason (1947).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>21.11.83.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith, dear Mr. Jackson, I beg to send you a copy of part of a letter from Dr. Fournier, just received,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See E. Fournier to M, 24 September 1883 (in this edition as 83-09-24a).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> concerning the priority of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Vahea">Vahea</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> over <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Landolphia">Landolphia</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>, as this question will interest you not only for these genera but in many other respects for your nomenclator.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Index Kewessis, </seg>
                     <seg style="">B. Jackson (1895)</seg>
                     <seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I also forward a copy of the important prospectus, found by Dr. Fournier, as this renders it conclusive, how far the “illustration des genres”<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Lamarck (1791–1823). See also M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 3 January 1882.</p>
               </note> had actually appeared up to 1796. As you and Mr. Britten<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>James Britten.</p>
               </note> took such an interest in clearing up the dates of Rees’ Cyclopedia,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Rees (1819-20). See B. Jackson (1877) and B. Jackson (1880a); but see also Pestana (1979) for a critique of Jackson's analysis.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> you likely will give some attention to this question now.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I intended to have written a letter on the subject in Trimen’s journal or rather now Britten’s journal of Botany, but I have been suffering for fully two months from so severe a bronchial catarrh, that I had to keep to my rooms all that time;<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had, <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>however, written an essay on nomenclature of </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Vahea">Vahea</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> in B82.09.01, which was republished in the </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of botany</seg>
                     <seg style=""> (B83.03.03) with an editorial introductory note: '</seg>The following note was communicated by Baron von Mueller to the Melbourne ' Chemist and Druggist ' for September, 1882, and seems to us of sufficient interest to deserve wider circulation'. <seg style="">Britten had taken over from Trimen as editor of the </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of botany</seg>
                     <seg style=""> in 1879.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> the cough has slightly abated now, but as there is some emphysema, it is doubtful whether I will recover. My parents both died early on phthisis, and hereditary inclination to that fatal disease brought me out to this warmer clime as soon as I left the University. In the wet season it is however even here too cold for me. I am just going up into a solid forest region with the hope of benefitting from the moist equable air there. I feel very weak. Am very sorry to hear of Mr. Bentham’s failing strength, but hope, that after some rest he will still be able to resume his great phytographic labours.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham in effect gave up botany at about this time; see G. Bentham to M, November 1883 (in this edition as 83-11-00). Bentham died on 10 September 1884.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Landolphia">Landolphia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Vahea">Vahea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
